    "Influence analysis emerged alongside the initial study of linear models and regression (Jaeckel, 1972; Cook & Weisberg, 1982).",
    "The insights gained from early influence analysis contributed to the development of numerous methods that improved model robustness and reduced model sensitivity to training outliers (Hogg, 1979; Rousseeuw, 1994)."
